video_title: Swapnil Jain - AI Agents for CX - SuperAI Singapore 2025
description:
Learn more about SuperAI: superai.com
Follow us on X: x.com/superai_conf

Keynote: AI Agents for CX

Speaker:
Swapnil Jain, Co-Founder and CEO @ Observe.AI

Stage: WEKA Stage
#superai #observeai #customerservice #customerexperience #ai

Recorded on 19 June 2025

transcript.aggregated_text: hello everyone i'm Swapnil i'm the founder and CEO of observe.ai you obviously heard a lot about compute storage GPUs Nvidia and so on what I'm going to talk to you about a real world application of AI agents that you're going to experience very very soon in your life when we think about AI and when we think about applications some of the biggest markets to apply these technologies exist in customer support last year alone customer service was a $400 billion spend for businesses businesses globally would hire these human agents i'm going to say human just to not confuse with AI agents would hire these human agents to do customer service these people are sitting obviously all over the world handling queries when we have a problem when a package gets delayed we call them when we need a healthcare appointment we call them there's a big spend last year and the interesting thing about the work that happens in customer support and customer service is what it what makes it very very unique for AI agents customer service is a very repetitive job you talk to a person working in customer support and customer service and they will tell you they handle 50 calls in a day and a big majority of them were very similar where's my package when will I get my return you know can I refer this package and so on and so forth that makes it very very appealing for AI agents because AI looks for repeatability ai looks for something to do it again and again and again now while the cost is going up for customer service the challenge in the current model is that the customer experience is going down none of us wake up in the morning saying "I'm excited to call customer service." Never happens we don't wake up and say "Oh you know what my phone is not working my internet is not working and I'm super excited i'm going to call customer service no it's always very very dreadful we're always scared about talking to customer service because we know that we're going to be put on hold for a long time we might not be able to talk to them in one drive we might have to call them healthcare providers in the US the customer service agents are doing the same thing again and again and again in financial services you would look at things like account management banking checkings
